nclass GFG{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n// A utility function to swap two elements\r\nstatic void swap(int[] arr, int i, int j)\r\n{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;int temp = arr[i];\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;arr[i] = arr[j];\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;arr[j] = temp;\r\n}\r\n&nbsp;\r\n/* This function takes last element as pivot, places\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;the pivot element at its correct position in sorted\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;array, and places all smaller (smaller than pivot)\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;to left of pivot and all greater elements to right\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;of pivot */\r\nstatic int partition(int[] arr, int low, int high)\r\n{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// pivot\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;int pivot = arr[high];\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// Index of smaller element and\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// indicates the right position\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// of pivot found so far\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;int i = (low - 1);\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;for(int j = low; j &lt;= high - 1; j++)\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// If current element is smaller\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// than the pivot\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (arr[j] &lt; pivot)\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// Increment index of\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// smaller element\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;i++;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;swap(arr, i, j);\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;swap(arr, i + 1, high);\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return (i + 1);\r\n}\r\n&nbsp;\r\n/* The main function that implements QuickSort\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;arr[] --&gt; Array to be sorted,\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;low --&gt; Starting index,\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;high --&gt; Ending index\r\n&nbsp;*/\r\nstatic void quickSort(int[] arr, int low, int high)\r\n{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (low &lt; high)\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// pi is partitioning index, arr[p]\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// is now at right place\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;int pi = partition(arr, low, high);\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// Separately sort elements before\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;// partition and after partition\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;quickSort(arr, low, pi - 1);\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;quickSort(arr, pi + 1, high);\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}\r\n}\r\n&nbsp;\r\n// Function to print an array\r\nstatic void printArray(int[] arr, int size)\r\n{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;for(int i = 0; i &lt; size; i++)\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;System.out.print(arr[i] + \" \");\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;System.out.println();\r\n}\r\n&nbsp;\r\n// Driver Code\r\npublic static void main(String[] args)\r\n{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;int[] arr = { 10, 7, 8, 9, 1, 5 };\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;int n = arr.length;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;quickSort(arr, 0, n - 1);\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;System.out.println(\"Sorted array: \");\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;printArray(arr, n);\r\n}\r\n}\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</pre><h2>3.3 c√°c trang web h·ªçc thu·∫≠t to√°n</h2><p>hackerrank, leetcode, codelearn.io, freecodecamp...</p><p><img src=\"/images/posts/1/hackerrank_4142022T9236.png\"></p><h1>4. Code&nbsp;</h1><p>- Sau khi ƒë√£ h·ªçc nh·ªØng ki·∫øn th·ª©c th√¨ ch√∫ng ta n√™n Code ƒë·∫ßu ti√™n l√† nh·ªØng d·ª± √°n nh·ªè ƒë·ªÉ l√†m quen.</p><p>- sau ƒë√≥ l√† nh·ªØng d·ª± √°n l·ªõn k·∫øt h·ª£p nhi·ªÅu c√¥ng ngh·ªá l·∫°i v·ªõi nhau&nbsp;</p><p>- Ch√∫ng ta n√™n v·ª´a Code v·ª´a ƒë·ªçc document v√¨ nh∆∞ th·∫ø ch√∫ng ta s·∫ª nh·ªõ ki·∫øn th·ª©c l√¢u h∆°n</p><p>- Trong qu√° tr√¨nh Code ch√∫ng ta s·∫ª g·∫∑p nhi·ªÅu bug, nh∆∞ng kh√¥ng sao ƒë√£ c√≥ nh·ªØng c·ªông ƒë·ªìng l·∫≠p tr√¨nh vi√™n debug nh∆∞: stackoverflow, github...</p><p><br></p><p>hoanglinhplus website:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoanglinhplus.orgfree.com\" target=\"_blank\">hoanglinhplus</a></p><p>B√†i Vi·∫øt C√≤n Ti√™p....</p><p><br></p>',1,'2022-02-14 02:13:25','2022-05-14 02:22:25','2022-05-14 02:22:25'),(27,1,'Dependency Injection l√† g√¨ 123','Dependency_Injection_la_gi_123','B√†i vi·∫øt ƒëc d·ªãch t·ª´:¬†https://medium.freecodecamp.org/a-quick-intro-to-dependency-injection-what-it-is-and-when-to-use-it-7578c84fa88f','/images/posts/10/Dependency-Injection-ASP.NET-Core_4152022T73847.png','<p><br></p><h3><strong>Gi·ªõi thi·ªáu</strong></h3><p>Theo nh∆∞ ƒë·ªãnh nghƒ©a c·ªßa Wikipedia</p><blockquote>Dependency injection l√† m·ªôt kƒ© thu·∫≠t trong ƒë√≥ m·ªôt object (ho·∫∑c m·ªôt static method) cung c·∫•p c√°c dependencies c·ªßa m·ªôt object kh√°c. M·ªôt dependency l√† m·ªôt object m√† c√≥ th·ªÉ s·ª≠ d·ª•ng (m·ªôt service). Tuy nhi√™n ƒë·ªãnh nghƒ©a tr√™n v·∫´n kh√° l√† kh√≥ hi·ªÉu, v·∫≠y n√™n h√£y c√πng t√¨m hi·ªÉu ƒë·ªÉ hi·ªÉu r√µ h∆°n v·ªÅ n√≥ n√†o.</blockquote><p>Dependency hay dependent nghƒ©a l√† ph·ª• thu·ªôc v√†o h·ªó tr·ª£ c·ªßa m·ªôt c√°i g√¨, vi·ªác g√¨ ƒë√≥. V√≠ d·ª• nh∆∞ n·∫øu ch√∫ng ta ph·ª• thu·ªôc qu√° nhi·ªÅu v√†o smartphone, th√¨ c√≥ th·ªÉ hi·ªÉu l√† ch√∫ng ta ƒë√£ dependent l√™n smartphone.</p><p>Trc\' khi n√≥i v·ªÅ dependency injection, h√£y hi·ªÉu xem dependency trong l·∫≠p tr√¨nh nghƒ©a l√† g√¨ trc\'.</p><p>Khi m√† class A s·ª≠ d·ª•ng m·ªôt s·ªë ch·ª©c nƒÉng c·ªßa class class B, th√¨ c√≥ th·ªÉ n√≥i l√† class A c√≥ quan h·ªá ph·ª• thu·ªôc v·ªõi class B.<img src=\"https://images.viblo.asia/dd6d54c4-7fd4-48a0-a2ba-ec7ee0651949.jpeg\"></p><p>Trong java, trc\' khi ta c√≥ th·ªÉ s·ª≠ d·ª•ng method c·ªßa class kh√°c, ta ph·∫£i kh·ªüi t·∫°o m·ªôt object c·ªßa class ƒë·∫•y (hay A c·∫ßn ph·∫£i t·∫°o 1 th·ª±c th·ªÉ c·ªßa B).</p><p>V·∫≠y ta c√≥ th·ªÉ hi·ªÉu, vi·ªác chuy·ªÉn giao nhi·ªám v·ª• kh·ªüi t·∫°o object ƒë√≥ cho m·ªôt ai kh√°c v√† tr·ª±c ti·∫øp s·ª≠ d·ª•ng c√°c dependency ƒë√≥ ƒë∆∞·ª£c g·ªçi l√† dependency injection.<img src=\"https://images.viblo.asia/1057e16d-643e-4512-a6cc-2b6ce9cb9898.png\"></p><h3><strong>T·∫°i sao ch√∫ng ta c·∫ßn s·ª≠ d·ª•ng dependency injection?</strong></h3><p>V√≠ d·ª• ch√∫ng ta c√≥ m·ªôt class Car, trong ƒë√≥ c√≥ ch·ª©a m·ªôt v√†i object kh√°c nh∆∞ Wheel, Battery...</p><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">class Car{\r\n  private Wheels wheel = new MRFWheels();\r\n  private Battery battery = new ExcideBattery();\r\n  ...\r\n  ...\r\n}\r\n</pre><p>·ªû ƒë√¢y, class Car ch·ªãu tr√°ch nhi·ªám kh·ªüi t·∫°o t·∫•t c·∫£ c√°c dependency object. Nh∆∞ng chuy·ªán g√¨ s·∫Ω x·∫£y ra n·∫øu ch√∫ng ta mu·ªën b·ªè MRFWheel v√† thay th·∫ø b·∫±ng YokohamaWheel.</p><p>Ch√∫ng ta s·∫Ω c·∫ßn t·∫°o m·ªôt class Car m·ªõi v·ªõi YokohamaWheel, tuy nhi√™n khi s·ª≠ d·ª•ng dependency injection, ch√∫ng ta c√≥ th·ªÉ ƒë·ªïi Wheel ·ªü runtime v√¨ dependency c√≥ th·ªÉ ƒëc ƒë·∫©y v√†o (inject) ·ªü runtime thay v√¨ complile time.</p><p>B·∫°n c√≥ th·ªÉ hi·ªÉu l√† dependency injection l√† m·ªôt ng∆∞·ªùi trung gian ch·ªãu tr√°ch nhi·ªám t·∫°o ra c√°c lo·∫°i wheel kh√°c nhau, r·ªìi cung c·∫•p ch√∫ng cho class Car. Vi·ªác ƒë√≥ l√†m cho class Car ko ph·∫£i ph·ª• thu·ªôc v√†o Wheel c·ª• th·ªÉ n√†o hay Battery c·ª• th·ªÉ n√†o n·ªØa.</p><h3><strong>V·ªÅ c∆° b·∫£n c√≥ 3 lo·∫°i dependency injection:</strong></h3><ol><li><strong>Constructor injection</strong>: c√°c dependency ƒëc cung c·∫•p th√¥ng qua constructor c·ªßa class.</li><li><strong>Setter injection</strong>: client t·∫°o ra m·ªôt setter method ƒë·ªÉ c√°c class kh√°c c√≥ th·ªÉ s·ª≠ d·ª•ng ch√∫ng ƒë·ªÉ c·∫•p dependency.</li><li><strong>Interface injection</strong>: dependency s·∫Ω cung c·∫•p m·ªôt h√†m injector ƒë·ªÉ inject n√≥ v√†o b·∫•t k√¨ client n√†o ƒëc truy·ªÅn v√†o. C√°c client ph·∫£i implement m·ªôt interface m√† c√≥ m·ªôt setter method d√†nh cho vi·ªác nh·∫≠n dependency.</li></ol><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">class Car{\r\n  private Wheels wheel;\r\n  private Battery battery;\r\n  \r\n  /*·ªû ƒë√¢u ƒë√≥ trong project, ta kh·ªüi t·∫°o nh·ªØng objects m√† ƒëc y√™u c·∫ßu b·ªüi class n√†y\r\n    C√≥ 2 c√°ch ƒë·ªÉ implement dependency injection\r\n    1. D·ª±a v√†o constructor\r\n    2. D·ª±a v√†o Setter method\r\n  */\r\n  \r\n  // D·ª±a v√†o constructor\r\n  Car(Wheel wh, Battery bt) {\r\n    this.wh = wh;\r\n    this.bt = bt;\r\n  }\r\n  \r\n  // D·ª±a v√†o Setter method\r\n  void setWheel(Batter bt){\r\n    this.bt = bt;\r\n  }\r\n  ...  \r\n  ...\r\n}\r\n</pre><p>V·∫≠y tr√°ch nhi·ªám c·ªßa dependency injection l√†:</p><ol><li>T·∫°o ra c√°c object.</li><li>Bi·∫øt ƒë∆∞·ª£c class n√†o c·∫ßn nh·ªØng object ƒë·∫•y.</li><li>Cung c·∫•p cho nh·ªØng class ƒë√≥ nh·ªØng object ch√∫ng c·∫ßn.</li></ol><p>B·∫±ng c√°ch n√†y, n·∫øu trong t∆∞∆°ng lai object ƒë√≥ c√≥ s·ª± thay ƒë·ªïi th√¨ dependency injection c√≥ nhi·ªám v·ª• c·∫•p l·∫°i nh·ªØng object c·∫ßn thi·∫øt cho class.</p><h3><strong>L·ª£i √≠ch c·ªßa dependency injection.</strong></h3><ol><li>Gi√∫p vi·∫øt Unit test d·ªÖ d√†ng h∆°n.</li><li>Gi·∫£m thi·ªÉu ƒëc boilerplate code v√¨ vi·ªác kh·ªüi t·∫°o dependency ƒëc l√†m b·ªüi m·ªôt component kh√°c.</li><li>M·ªü d·ª•ng d·ª± √°n d·ªÖ d√†ng h∆°n.</li><li>Gi√∫p √≠ch trong vi·ªác li√™n k·∫øt l·ªèng (loose coupling) gi·ªØa c√°c th√†nh ph·∫ßn trong d·ª± √°n.</li></ol><h